Standard Terms and Conditions

1. Services

1.1 Engagement and Statements of Work. VanMobile hereby engages Contractor, and Contractor hereby accepts such engagement, for Contractor to perform consulting, Software development, design, application, training, integration, implementation and other professional services from time to time for VanMobile as described in one or more Statements of Work therefor and to provide and transfer any and all Work Product, Intellectual Property, and Intellectual Property Rights resulting therefrom to VanMobile all during the term of this Agreement and all on the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement and any and all such Statements of Work. Each Statement of Work shall be mutually agreed upon and signed by both parties.
Contractor shall determine the time, place, manner, and means of performing the Services and shall perform the Services in accordance with the schedule set forth in the applicable Statement of Work. No Statement of Work shall be effective unless signed by duly authorized Representatives of both parties. Each fully executed Statement of Work shall be attached as an Exhibit to, and by this reference incorporated in and made a part of, this Agreement. 

1.2 Change Orders; Conflicts. In the event either party requires a material change to a Statement of Work, such party will provide a written change order to the other for approval via email, specifying the change required (each a "Change Order"). Each party agrees that a Change Order may necessitate a change in the delivery schedule and fees due under the applicable Statement of Work. No Change Order will be binding upon either party until it is agreed upon in writing by email by authorized Representatives of both parties. Each Statement of Work and Change Order will be governed by the terms of this Agreement. In the event of a conflict between the terms and conditions of this Agreement and those of a Statement of Work or Change Order, the terms and conditions of this Agreement will control, unless specifically stated otherwise in the Statement of Work or Change Order. 

1.3 Acceptance, Rejection, and/or Modification of Work Product. Upon Contractorâ€™s submission of the Work Product, VanMobile will, in its sole discretion, accept or reject all or part of the Work Product or return it to Contractor with suggested changes. Contractor acknowledges that if the unaccepted portion of the Work Product contains any Confidential Information or VanMobile Materials, then VanMobile will retain sole and exclusive ownership of such property, and Contractor shall return the unaccepted Work Product to VanMobile. 
If VanMobile requires a change to the Work Product, it will notify Contractor of the requested change and the due date for resubmitting the revised Work Product. VanMobile may accept or reject all or part of the corrected Work Product at its sole discretion. VanMobile will have no obligation to return any accepted Work Product to Contractor. VanMobile has the right to edit or adapt any Work Product in any manner, including, without limitation, with respect to its form, medium, format, delivery mechanism or content as VanMobile deems appropriate. Contractor agrees to provide VanMobile with the information and know-how necessary for VanMobile to edit or adapt the Work Product, at no additional cost to VanMobile, and will cooperate with VanMobile in any such editing or adaptation.
If the Work Product is an article or other written piece, Contractor agrees to provide to VanMobile with the Work Product, a written bibliography and list of sources contacted in the process of researching and preparing such Work Product and include captions and pull quotes where appropriate. 

1.4 Time of the Essence. Contractor acknowledges that time is of the essence with respect to Contractor's obligations hereunder and agrees that prompt and timely performance of all such obligations in accordance with this Agreement and each Statement of Work is strictly required. 

1.5 Duties Regarding Performance, Work Product, and Software. Contractor shall design, develop, create, test, deliver, install, configure, integrate, customize and otherwise provide and make fully operational Work Product as described in each Statement of Work, and otherwise provide the Services, all in a timely, professional, workmanlike manner and in accordance with all terms, conditions and business, functional, and technical specifications set forth in this Agreement and any such Statement of Work. Contractor shall ensure all Work Product complies with the specifications therefor as set forth in the applicable Statement of Work. Contractor shall provide all Software to VanMobile in either or both object code and Source Code form at the sole option of VanMobile. 

1.6 Third-Party Materials. Unless expressly provided otherwise in any applicable Statement of Work, Contractor shall not include in any Software, and operation of all Software in accordance with its specifications shall not require, any Third-Party Materials. 

1.7 Background Technology. Unless expressly provided otherwise in any applicable Statement of Work, Contractor shall not include in any Software, and operation of all Software in accordance with its specifications shall not require, any Background Technology. 

1.8 Open-Source Components. Contractor may include in any Software, and operation of any Software in accordance with its specifications as set forth in any applicable Statement of Work may require the use of, any Open-Source Components. 

1.9 Controlled Technology. Contractor shall not include in any Software any Controlled Technology. 

1.10 Contractor Personnel. 
a) Contractor is solely responsible for all Contractor Personnel and for the payment of their compensation, including, if applicable, withholding of income taxes, and the payment and withholding of social security and other payroll taxes, unemployment insurance, workers' compensation insurance payments and disability benefits. 
b) Prior to any Contractor Personnel performing any Services hereunder, Contractor shall: 
i. ensure that such Contractor Personnel have the legal right to work; and 
ii. require such Contractor Personnel to execute written agreements, in form and substance acceptable to VanMobile, that bind such Contractor Personnel to confidentiality provisions that are at least as protective of VanMobile's information (including all Confidential Information) as those contained in this Agreement and Intellectual Property Rights provisions that grant VanMobile rights in the Work Product consistent with the provisions of Section 3 and, upon VanMobile's request, provide VanMobile such executed agreement(s). 
c) Contractor shall, and shall ensure that all Contractor Personnel, comply with all rules, regulations and policies of VanMobile that are communicated to Contractor in writing, including security procedures concerning systems and data and remote access thereto. 

1.11 Testing By Contractor. Before delivering and installing any Work Product, Contractor shall test any Software component of the Work Product to confirm that it is fully operable, meets all applicable specifications in the applicable Statement of Work, and will function properly, and shall also scan such Software component of the Work Product using the most up-to-date scanning software and definitions to confirm it is free of Harmful Code before delivery to VanMobile. Any Harmful Code identified must be remedied before delivery and the Software component of the Work Product must be retested and rescanned. 


2. Fees and Payment 

2.1 Fees. In consideration of the rights granted and Services provided by Contractor hereunder, subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement and the applicable Statement of Work, VanMobile agrees to pay Contractor all fees due pursuant to Statements of Work entered into hereunder, subject to timely submission of any deliverables in accordance with the schedule in the applicable Statement of Work, as set forth in this Section 2. Contractor will provide VanMobile with reasonable documentation and work description in connection with Contractorâ€™s invoices, as requested by VanMobile. 

2.2 Costs and Expenses. Unless expressly provided otherwise in any applicable Statement of Work, Contractor will be solely responsible for all expenses incurred by Contractor or any of its employees or agents or subcontractors in connection with performing the Services or otherwise performing its obligations under this Agreement. 

2.3 Payment Terms. Except as otherwise set forth herein or in a Statement of Work, Contractor will invoice VanMobile on a periodic basis for amounts due hereunder which periodic basis will be determined by VanMobile from time to time, and VanMobile shall pay invoices as set forth in the applicable Statement of Work. All payments will be made in U.S. dollars at VanMobileâ€™s option and by a payment method of VanMobileâ€™s choosing. 
Contractor shall submit each invoice in PDF format via email to an email address as specified by VanMobile in writing from time to time. If more than one Statement of Work is outstanding, Contractor shall provide an aggregate invoice for all fees being invoiced, together with separate invoices for each Statement of Work. All time must be tracked in Harvest or the then-current time tracking software application specified by VanMobile from time to time. Each separate invoice shall be generated in Harvest or the then-current time tracking software application specified by VanMobile from time to time and shall also: 
a) identify the Statement of Work to which the invoice relates, in a manner determined by VanMobile; 
b) include detailed notes for each line item; 
c) for fees determined on a time and materials basis, report details of time taken to perform Services, and such other information that VanMobile requires, on a per-individual basis; 
d) be accompanied by all supporting documentation required hereunder for reimbursable expenses; and e) include such other information as may be required by VanMobile as set forth in the applicable Statement of Work. 

Contractor shall be responsible for all wire and transfer fees. 
Payments shall be made to the address or account as is specified by Contractor in writing from time to time, provided that Contractor shall give VanMobile at least seven (7) days' prior notice of any account, address or other change in payment instructions. VanMobile will not be liable for any late or misdirected payment caused by Contractor's failure to provide timely notice of any such change. 
VanMobile may withhold from payment any amount disputed by VanMobile in good faith, pending resolution of any dispute. Contractor shall continue performing its obligations in accordance with this Agreement notwithstanding any such dispute or actual or alleged nonpayment that is the subject of a dispute, pending its resolution. 

2.4 Taxes. All fees set forth herein are exclusive of taxes. Contractor shall be responsible for all sales, use and excise taxes, and any other similar taxes, duties and charges of any kind imposed by any federal, provincial/state or local governmental entity on any amounts payable by VanMobile hereunder other than any taxes imposed on, or with respect to, Contractor's income, revenues, gross receipts, personnel or real or personal property or other assets. 

2.5 Right of Set-off. Without prejudice to any other right or remedy it may have, VanMobile reserves the right to set off at any time any amount owing to it by Contractor against any amount payable by VanMobile to Contractor under this Agreement or otherwise. 


3. Intellectual Property Rights Ownership; Licenses

3.1 VanMobile Ownership of Work Product. Except as set forth in Section 3.3 and 3.7, VanMobile is and will be the sole and exclusive owner of all right, title and interest in and to all Work Product, including all Intellectual Property Rights therein. In furtherance of the foregoing, subject to Section 3.3 and 3.7: 
a) Contractor shall create all Work Product as work made for hire as defined in Section 101 of the Copyright Act of 1976; and 
