c) in connection with the performance of Services, to Contractorâ€™s legal counsel and accountants who, in the Contractorâ€™s reasonable judgment, need to know the 
Confidential Information and agree to be bound by the provisions of Section 6 as if a party. 
Contractor must not make any disclosure permitted by this Section (other than disclosure to Contractorâ€™s own legal counsel in connection with the performance of Services) before notifying VanMobile as far in advance of the disclosure as practicable. Notice to VanMobile must state the purpose of the disclosure and the means taken to ensure that any disclosed Confidential Information remains confidential. 


7. Term and Termination

7.1 Term. This Agreement shall become effective upon the Effective Date for a term of twelve (12) months (the "Initial Term"), unless terminated as provided herein. Following the Initial Term, this Agreement shall automatically renew for one (1) month terms (each a "Renewal Term") unless either party provides notice of its intent not to renew the Agreement. To be effective, such notice must be delivered at least five (5) days in advance of the next Renewal Term. 

7.2 Termination. Notwithstanding subsection 7.1, VanMobile may terminate this Agreement with or without cause upon seven (7) days' notice to Contractor, and must pay Contractor within thirty (30) days of the date of termination for all previously-accrued but not yet paid fees for acceptable Services performed and deliverables completed to that date. Either VanMobile or Contractor may terminate this Agreement if the other is in material breach and has not cured this material breach within thirty (30) days of receipt of written notice specifying the breach. 

7.3 
Effect of Termination. Upon the expiration or termination of this Agreement, 
(a) each party shall return the otherâ€™s Confidential Information in its possession or control, and 
(b) all amounts owed to Contractor under this Agreement which accrued before such termination or expiration, for Services and Work Product deliverables that have been accepted by VanMobile in accordance with the applicable Statement of Work, will be immediately due and payable. 
Sections 2 (Fees and Payment), 3 (Intellectual Property Rights Ownership; Licenses), 4 (Warranties), 5 (Indemnification), 6 (Confidentiality), 7.3 (Effect of Termination), 8 (Limitation of Liability), 9 (Non-Solicitation), 10 (Nondisparagement), 11 (General), and 12 (Definitions) will survive the expiration or termination of this Agreement for any reason. 
Upon the termination of this Agreement, Contractor will provide reasonable assistance to VanMobile for the transition of Services and Work Product deliverables in accordance with VanMobileâ€™s reasonable requirements. 


